<div class="blog-faq">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Is cosmetic surgery safe for older patients?</h3>
<p>Age alone is not necessarily a contraindication for cosmetic surgery. Many older patients undergo procedures safely. The key factors are overall health, medical conditions, and the ability to tolerate anesthesia. A thorough pre-operative evaluation will determine if a patient is a suitable candidate for surgery regardless of age.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What is the most dangerous plastic surgery procedure?</h3>
<p>All surgical procedures carry some degree of risk. The risk level depends on the complexity of the procedure, the patient's health, and the surgeon's experience. Body contouring and combined procedures tend to have slightly higher complication rates due to longer surgery times. Choosing a board-certified surgeon significantly minimizes risks across all procedures.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How can I verify if a surgeon is board-certified?</h3>
<p>You can verify a surgeon's board certification by checking with the relevant medical board in your country. In India, you can verify credentials through the Medical Council of India or the Association of Plastic Surgeons of India. Dr. Johar's certifications and awards are publicly listed on his website for full transparency.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What should I do if I experience complications after surgery?</h3>
<p>Contact your surgeon immediately if you experience any signs of complications, such as excessive swelling, unusual pain, fever, or changes in skin color. Most complications, when caught early, can be effectively managed. Dr. Johar provides 24/7 post-operative support to ensure that any concerns are addressed promptly.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Are non-surgical cosmetic procedures safer than surgery?</h3>
<p>Non-surgical procedures like Botox, fillers, and chemical peels generally carry lower risks than surgical procedures. However, they are not risk-free. Complications can still occur, especially when performed by untrained practitioners. Always choose a qualified medical professional for any cosmetic treatment, whether surgical or non-surgical.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How long does recovery take after plastic surgery?</h3>
<p>Recovery time varies depending on the procedure. Minor procedures may require only a few days of recovery, while more complex surgeries may take two to six weeks. Following your surgeon's post-operative instructions carefully is the best way to ensure a smooth and timely recovery.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Can I combine multiple plastic surgery procedures in one operation?</h3>
<p>Yes, combining procedures is common and can reduce overall recovery time and costs. However, the total surgical time must be carefully considered to minimize anesthesia risks. Dr. Johar evaluates each patient individually to determine whether combining procedures is safe and appropriate.</p>
</div>
</div>

